## 🚨 Notes & Observations

> [!WARNING]
> **[RoleController](file:///d:/alpha/dotnet/dotnet.calcifer/src/Calcifer.Api/v1/Controllers/AuthController/RoleController.cs#9-35) authorization is commented out** — the `[Authorize(Roles = "Admin")]` attribute on line 11 is disabled. Both `POST /api/Role/create` and `POST /api/Role/assign` are currently open to anyone.

> [!NOTE]
> **Duplicate [ApiResponseDto](file:///d:/alpha/dotnet/dotnet.calcifer/src/Calcifer.Api/v1/DTOs/HelperDTO/ApiResponseDto.cs#3-9)** — exists in both `v1.DTOs` and `v1.DTOs.HelperDTO` namespaces with identical structure. The minimal APIs use the `HelperDTO` version while controllers use the `DTOs` version.

> [!NOTE]
> **Dead code in `AuthController.Login`** — there is an unreachable `return Ok();` on line 40 after the ternary return on line 39.

> [!NOTE]
> **Dual project structure** — [Calcifer.Api.csproj](file:///d:/alpha/dotnet/dotnet.calcifer/src/Calcifer.Api/Calcifer.Api.csproj) (net10.0) wraps the actual [v1/v1.csproj](file:///d:/alpha/dotnet/dotnet.calcifer/src/Calcifer.Api/v1/v1.csproj) (net8.0). The outer project contains only a boilerplate weather forecast endpoint and is not the running application.

> [!TIP]
> **Startup sequence**: [Program.cs](file:///d:/alpha/dotnet/dotnet.calcifer/src/Calcifer.Api/Program.cs) → `DependencyInversion.RegisterServices()` → EF Core configuration → Identity + JWT setup → CORS → Build → Seed DB via `DatabaseInitializer.Initialize()` → Swagger → `MapControllers()` + [ApplicationMinimalApis()](file:///d:/alpha/dotnet/dotnet.calcifer/src/Calcifer.Api/v1/Middleware/MiddlewareDependencyInversion.cs#20-54) → Run.
